Kano State governor, Dr. Abdullahi Umar Ganduje on Sunday congratulated Isah Nasidi, an indigene of Kano state for developing a communication model to track fake news. Nasidi, a PhD student of Mass Communication, from the University of Nigeria Nsukka (UNN), developed a model called Source, Agent, Message, Channel, Audience and Victim (SAMCAV) to identify fake news. He is also the Secretary of Communication History Division of International Communication Association, based in the United States of America (USA). Private: 2023: Ganduje Under Fire Over Remarks About Tinubu Appeal Court Victory, Huge Relief – Ganduje Governor Ganduje in a statement by his Chief Press Secretary, Malam Abba Anwar said “As a young man who achieved this level in communication study, and an indigene of Kano state, I am pleased to, on behalf of the government and people of the state congratulate Isah Nasidi,” governor said. Ganduje said the young researcher-developed what is needed the most, “…at this era of information distortions for personal benefits or other reasons. I can understand that his Model links six elements of information disorder. He explained that the Source, Agent, Message, Channel, Audience and Victim (SAMCAV) would further discover the concept of dis-information, as the fourth type of information disorder. Dr. Ganduje while commending Nasidi for the bright scholarly contribution to the media study, similarly praised the Nigerian media for popularizing the author of the new communication model. That, “By this singular act of popularizing the work of this young researcher, it clearly indicates that, Nigerian media practitioners are very much concerned about the raging fake news in the public domain.”